#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "Billable Model"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:117
msgid ""
"Before using Cashier, add the `Billable` trait to your billable model "
"definition. Typically, this will be the `App\\Models\\User` model. This "
"trait provides various methods to allow you to perform common billing tasks, "
"such as creating subscriptions, applying coupons, and updating payment "
"method information:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "    use Laravel\\Cashier\\Billable;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    class User extends Authenticatable\n"
"    {\n"
"        use Billable;\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:126
msgid ""
"Cashier assumes your billable model will be the `App\\Models\\User` class "
"that ships with Laravel. If you wish to change this you can specify a "
"different model in your `.env` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "    CASHIER_MODEL=App\\Models\\User\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "> {note} If you're using a model other than Laravel's supplied `App\\Models\\User` model, you'll need to publish and alter the [Cashier migrations](#installation) provided to match your alternative model's table name.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"api-keys\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "API Keys"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:135
msgid ""
"Next, you should configure your Stripe API keys in your application's `.env` "
"file. You can retrieve your Stripe API keys from the Stripe control panel:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    STRIPE_KEY=your-stripe-key\n"
"    STRIPE_SECRET=your-stripe-secret\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:140
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"currency-configuration\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:140
#, no-wrap
msgid "Currency Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:143
msgid ""
"The default Cashier currency is United States Dollars (USD). You can change "
"the default currency by setting the `CASHIER_CURRENCY` environment variable "
"within your application's `.env` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "    CASHIER_CURRENCY=eur\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:147
msgid ""
"In addition to configuring Cashier's currency, you may also specify a locale "
"to be used when formatting money values for display on invoices. Internally, "
"Cashier utilizes [PHP's `NumberFormatter` class](https://www.php.net/manual/"
"en/class.numberformatter.php) to set the currency locale:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "    CASHIER_CURRENCY_LOCALE=nl_BE\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "> {note} In order to use locales other than `en`, ensure the `ext-intl` PHP extension is installed and configured on your server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"logging\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:156
msgid ""
"Cashier allows you to specify the log channel to be used when logging all "
"Stripe related exceptions. You may specify the log channel by defining the "
"`CASHIER_LOGGER` environment variable within your application's `.env` file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:158
#, no-wrap
msgid "    CASHIER_LOGGER=stack\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"using-custom-models\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using Custom Models"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:163
msgid ""
"You are free to extend the models used internally by Cashier by defining "
"your own model and extending the corresponding Cashier model:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "    use Laravel\\Cashier\\Subscription as CashierSubscription;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    class Subscription extends CashierSubscription\n"
"    {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:172
msgid ""
"After defining your model, you may instruct Cashier to use your custom model "
"via the `Laravel\\Cashier\\Cashier` class. Typically, you should inform "
"Cashier about your custom models in the `boot` method of your application's "
"`App\\Providers\\AppServiceProvider` class:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    use App\\Models\\Cashier\\Subscription;\n"
"    use App\\Models\\Cashier\\SubscriptionItem;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/8.x/billing.md:186
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    /**\n"
"     * Bootstrap any application services.\n"
"     *\n"
"     * @return void\n"
"     */\n"
"    public function boot()\n"
"    {\n"
"        Cashier::useSubscriptionModel(Subscription::class);\n"
"        Cashier::useSubscriptionItemModel(SubscriptionItem::class);\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

